EX-Kano State Governor Ibrahim Shekarau was, yesterday, detained at the Kano office of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC). Detained with the former minister of Education is ex-Minister of Foreign Affairs Aminu Wali, and Mansur Ahmad, for alleged criminal conspiracy and money laundering. TheyÂ  were quizzed for over an hour and released on Tuesday. Yesterday, the EFCC detained them for possible arraignment today at the Federal High Court in Kano. Shekarau is accused of collecting N25 million from the N950 million logistics money for 2015 elections.